  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F.",
    "Season sea bass fillets with salt and pepper. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle red pepper flakes over them.",
    "Sauté garlic and onion in a pan until soft, about 2 minutes. Add tomato sauce and cook for another 3-4 minutes.",
    "Place fish on top of the sauce mixture, then cover with breadcrumbs mixed with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through.",
